svg.text: The Glia Tourniquet - Instructions For Use

tspan.tspan: The tourniquet should come
staged with the strap already
If your tourniquet is not staged
prior to use, simply thread the
strap through the buckle and
Place the injured limb through
the tourniquet and place the
tourniquet approximately 75mm
Where possible, the tourniquet
should be placed directly on bare
Tighten the strap as much as
possible before securing it using
the hook and loop fasteners on
three half revolutions. If severe

text.tspan: windlass as in the following steps
above the first as quickly as

tspan.tspan: Further secure the windlass into
the clip by wrapping the main
strap over the windlass and
securing it to itself, then wrap the
white hook and loop strap over
the main strap which is securing
the windlass in the clip and fasten
it to the black hook and loop strip

text.tspan: Record the time of the application.
